Setup environment

[main.js]

- Get express
- create app/server
- Define a PORT: 8080
- Get mongoose
- Define connection string
- Try to connect with mongoose and get my connection
    * Make mongoose when errors arise
    * Make mongoose tell me when it is connected

- Define my mongoose models
- Define API endpoints on my express app
- Start listening for requests on my express app

[express endpoint /students get]
- Get student models
- Find all documents in the models
- If there is an error
    * Status = 400
    * Display error message
- else
    *Display documents found

[express endpoint /students post]
- Get the body from the request
- Create a new instance of the model students
- Save new instance
    * If successful
        # display message to client
    * If error
        # status = 400
        # Display error message

[express endpoint /students/:id get]
- Get parameter id from request
- Get student model
- Find by id in the model
    * If there is an error
        #status = 400
        #Display error message
    * else
        # Display document found

[endpoint endpoint /students/:id put]
- Get parameter id from request
- Get student model
- Find by id in the model
    * If there is an error
        #status = 400
        #Display error message
    * else
        # Get the body from request
        # Use the document we found and asign the new data
            **Student.firstName = body.firstName
            **Student.lastName = body.lastName
            **Student.email = body.email
        # Save changes in the document

[express endpoint /students/:id delete]
- Get parameter id from request
- Get Student model
- Find by id in the model
    *If there is an error
        #status = 400
        #Display error message
    *else
        #Delete message
            @if successful (then)
                & display message
            @if error(catch)
